Press Release<br /><!-- NewsDate.start -->February 28, 2007<!-- NewsDate.end --><p>
<span class="PRTitle"><!-- NewsTitle.start -->PING: CHECKERED SHIRTS STAND <br />FOR HARD WORK, COURAGE, DETERMINATION<!-- NewsTitle.end --></span></p>
<!-- NewsBody.start --><p style="text-align: justify">AGOO, La Union  As they connote hard work and determination, checkered polo shirts are re-electionist Sen. Panfilo Lacsons trademark apparel in his sorties.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify">Lacson told reporters that aside from having gotten used to the shirts since his days in the Philippine National Police, checkered patterns are a symbol of hard work and determination.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify">For me, checkered shirts exude courage and connote hard work and determination, and thats what I am.  When I work I work hard and Im determined to accomplish things, he said.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify">He said this was the work ethic he showed when he headed the Philippine National Police (PNP) from 1999 to 2001, and when he became a senator in 2001.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify">He said that when he was head of the defunct Presidential Anti-Crime Commission Task Force Habagat and when he headed the PNP, he was already fond of wearing such shirts.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify">But he admitted that he may have to play second fiddle to Rep. Alan Peter Cayetano, his fellow opposition senatorial bet, in terms of having a colorful life at this time.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify">Lacson was referring to Cayetanos being the target of first gentleman Jose Miguel Arroyo over Cayetanos claims of bank accounts members of the first family supposedly maintain abroad.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify">On the other hand, he said he will never be caught dead wearing shirts with floral prints.</p>
